    <item>
      <title>美联储和债券卫士成为特朗普新时代的焦点</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2024-11-07/fed-and-bond-vigilantes-take-center-stage-in-trump-s-new-era</link>
      <description><![CDATA[唐纳德·特朗普当选的直接影响之一是：华尔街经济学家现在认为，考虑到特朗普的政策可能产生的通胀效应，美联储决策者将维持比原本更高的利率。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/newsletters/2024-11-07/fed-and-bond-vigilantes-take-center-stage-in-trump-s-new-era</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 Nov 2024 11:30:46 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>特朗普获胜对俄乌战争、中东紧张局势意味着什么 | 彭博社《脉搏》 11/07/24</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-07/global-leaders-grapple-with-trump-win-impact-the-pulse-video</link>
      <description><![CDATA[唐纳德·特朗普与世界领导人的关系将影响全球事件。这位美国当选总统可能会破坏北约盟国的团结，并使对乌克兰的援助前景蒙上阴影。中国是华盛顿罕见的两党共同攻击目标，而新一届特朗普政府正瞄准中国，呼吁对中国商品征收高达 60% 的关税。在中东，以色列可能会更加大胆地回应哈马斯、真主党和伊朗。总理本雅明·内塔尼亚胡在 X 上发帖致“亲爱的唐纳德和梅拉尼娅·特朗普”时迅速称赞这是“历史上最伟大的回归！”（来源：彭博社）]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/videos/2024-11-07/global-leaders-grapple-with-trump-win-impact-the-pulse-video</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 Nov 2024 11:18:07 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>尽管股东因收购退出而获得的收益放缓，凯雷仍提高了利润率</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-07/carlyle-boosts-margins-even-as-shareholder-earnings-from-buyout-exits-slow</link>
      <description><![CDATA[凯雷集团首席执行官哈维·施瓦茨 (Harvey Schwartz) 在第三季度提升了利润率和费用收益方面取得了进展，而在此期间，公司从交易退出中获得的股东利润仍然较低。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-07/carlyle-boosts-margins-even-as-shareholder-earnings-from-buyout-exits-slow</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 Nov 2024 11:01:00 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>塞尔维亚维持利率不变以应对价格压力</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-07/serbia-maintains-hold-on-rates-as-it-weighs-price-pressures</link>
      <description><![CDATA[塞尔维亚央行维持借贷成本不变，这一意外举措表明政策制定者在权衡持续的价格压力时采取了谨慎态度。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-07/serbia-maintains-hold-on-rates-as-it-weighs-price-pressures</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 Nov 2024 11:00:21 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>对德国债务狂潮的担忧首次成为关键市场指标</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-07/fear-of-german-debt-binge-flips-key-market-gauge-for-first-time</link>
      <description><![CDATA[在德国财政部长克里斯蒂安·林德纳 (Christian Lindner) — — 财政保守派的代表 — — 被解职后，交易员们为德国可能出售更多债券做好了准备，这导致一些市场人士开始考虑一个可能对高债务更加容忍的新政府。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-07/fear-of-german-debt-binge-flips-key-market-gauge-for-first-time</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 Nov 2024 09:31:39 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>日产汽车下调业绩预期，宣布重组并裁员 9,000 人</title>
      <link>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-07/nissan-cuts-outlook-announces-restructing-with-9-000-job-cuts</link>
      <description><![CDATA[日产汽车公司在应对汽车行业日益严峻的形势和解决业务内部弱点方面遇到的困难不断加剧，迫使该公司别无选择，只能削减工资、产量并降低本财年的预期。]]></description>
      <guid>https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2024-11-07/nissan-cuts-outlook-announces-restructing-with-9-000-job-cuts</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 07 Nov 2024 07:53:36 GMT</pubDate>
    </item>
